GlassBench

This dataset accompanies the "Roadmap on machine learning glassy liquids". This roadmap provides short reviews, extended benchmarking and future directions of different topics in which machine learning can assist us in better understanding deeply supercooled liquids and the glass transition. The roadmap in combination with this dataset will help to compare new techniques to the state-of-the-art and should therefore enable and encourage a broader community effort to further develop new ML approaches.

This dataset contains two different systems, the three-dimensional Kob-Andersen mixture (KA) and the two-dimensional ternary mixture (KA2D). For each system, we provide the pure simulation data (_trajectories), model predictions and derived structural properties (_models), as well as scripts to evaluate the data and reproduce the figures in the roadmap (_results). Detailed information on the separate datasets is provided in each of the six folders.

The dataset is uploaded with the license "Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International" which allows re-distribution and re-use of a licensed work on the condition that the creator is appropriately credited. If you use this dataset please cite the following works:

Title: Roadmap on machine learning glassy liquids
Authors: Gerhard Jung, Rinske Alkemade, Victor Bapst, Daniele Coslovich, Laura Filion, Francois P. Landes, Andrea Liu, Francesco Saverio Pezzicoli, Hayato Shiba, Giovanni Volpe, Francesco Zamponi, Ludovic Berthier and Giulio Biroli
Journal: TBA
